Ok. We are very tired and are going to take a nap now. Stay healthy!

snippet.textDisplay:
Friends, there is something urgent I would like to share with you all.

The Corona outbreak has made something very clear, our mortality. Masses our dying left and right daily because of the disease, never for this generation has death seemed so close. Yet the truth is death is always near, whether there is a disease or not. You and I can stay perfectly healthy and stay in our house for the rest of our lives, yet we will still die. Because all have an appointment with death, and once we die everything we worked for is gone, our money, our dreams, everything we own is gone.

The only thing that will matter is our place with God. In the beginning, God created the Heaven and the Earth, and over six days he created all life and every good thing. He created the first humans in his image, Adam and Eve, and they were gifted his perfect world to rule over with him. But they betrayed the God who gave them life, seeking to rule the world by their own rules and wisdom. This was the first sin, which led to death and pain in the world. For the wages of sin is death, our imperfectness and evil leads to only destruction and death. But God made a promise, that someday there would be a man that would destroy evil, but in turn, would take a fatal injury from evil. And because God is holy and just, there must be punishment for evil, there must be justice for our wrongs. Which is why there will be a day in which you and I, and everyone who has ever lived will be judged by his perfect law, the ten commandments. And all will be guilty because by breaking even one law you have broken them all, for you have become a lawbreaker. Have you ever lied? Have you ever dishonored your parents? Have you ever used God’s name in vain? Have you ever looked at someone with lust? If you have broken even one of these laws you are guilty. And the guilty will be sentenced to eternal punishment, for all liars, blasphemers, thieves, and adulterers have their part in the lake of fire. This is what we earn from our sins.

But there is good news. God is rich in mercy and love, and he is faithful in his promise to deliver a savior. 2000 years ago he sent his son, known as Jesus Christ as payment for our sins. He lived the perfect life that we should’ve lived, and ultimately paid the sacrifice we deserved. He took up our sins on the cross, and God poured out his wrath on him, and ultimately he died on the cross, with his final words being, “It is finished”. But on the third day, he rose from the dead and defeated the chains of sin and death. And whoever puts their faith in him will not perish, but have eternal life. So please, put your trust in Jesus and turn away from your sin, living a new life blameless through the power of the cross. For we have broken God’s law but he has made a way for us to be made right with him, and walk in the light of righteousness. I tell you these things out of love because I wish to see no one perish. But I warn you, God may have excused you before because you did not know these things, but now that I have told you the truth he will hold you accountable. Because what I have told you is the revelation of Jesus Christ that has the power to bring those who are in darkness out of light. So please turn to him, he is the only way. Our days are counting down, any moment could be our last so please turn to him.

If anyone has any questions I will gladly answer them to the best of my ability.
